.TH DBX-COMPLETION 1 "2026-06-02" "dbx 0.28.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
dbx-completion \- print a shell completion script
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B dbx completion
.IR bash | zsh | fish
.SH DESCRIPTION
Print a sourceable shell completion script for
.BR bash ,
.BR zsh ,
or
.BR fish .
TAB completion covers host aliases, databases, vault keys, restore
candidates from
.IR $DATA_DIR ,
schedule shorthands (daily / hourly / weekly / daily@HH / weekly@DOW:HH),
and per-command long flags.
.PP
Dynamic data comes from a hidden
.B "dbx __complete"
subcommand the generated script invokes on every TAB press; it reads
.IR config.json
and walks
.IR $DATA_DIR
but never touches docker or the network, so TAB latency stays low.
.PP
Restore completions emit only
.IR <host>/<database>/latest
rows by default. Once the partial has 3+ path components, the script
drills into that one host/db and emits specific filenames so you can
TAB-complete a timestamp.
.SH EXAMPLES
bash:
.PP
.RS
.nf
echo 'eval "$(dbx completion bash)"' >> ~/.bashrc
.fi
.RE
.PP
zsh (requires
.B "autoload -U compinit && compinit"
earlier in
.IR .zshrc ):
.PP
.RS
.nf
echo 'eval "$(dbx completion zsh)"' >> ~/.zshrc
.fi
.RE
.PP
fish:
.PP
.RS
.nf
dbx completion fish > ~/.config/fish/completions/dbx.fish
.fi
.RE
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR dbx (1),
.BR bash (1),
.BR zsh (1),
.BR fish (1).
